@Chris

Is it possible you really didn’t fully understand the theme?  Maybe that’s why the pairs seemed like long reaches to you. The complete clues aren’t supposed to be synonymous with the complete answers. For example, [Lottery commission?] isn’t supposed to be synonymous with DRAWING BOARD. “Lottery” is synonymous with “drawing,” and “commission” with “board.”  

Once I got the trick, every one of the themers seemed perfectly fine to me.

